        Notification small icon — monochrome shield silhouette.
        Android uses this as an alpha mask: the shape must be fully opaque (#FF000000)
        and the background transparent. The system then tints it white in the status bar
        and applies the notification accent color in the expanded view.
        Do NOT use white (#FFFFFFFF) here — that defeats the alpha-mask behaviour.
    -->
